title: Moments - The Best Of - 1996
description:
The Moments - The Best of The Moments: Love on a Two-Way Street (320)

The Moments released their first single, "Not on the Outside" in 1968 and charted regularly through the 1970s.  Their biggest hit was "Love on a Two-Way Street" in 1970, along with lesser hits "If I Didn't Care" and "All I Have."  Other hits included "Sexy Mama" in 1973 and "Look at Me (I'm in Love)" in 1975.  In 1978 they changed their billing to Ray, Goodman, & Brown and topped the soul lists in 1979 with "Special Lady."
